From 87eff91f1bfe3b3327d1dc2cc0a3eec908395b86 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Date: Sun, 6 Mar 2022 22:57:48 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] batman-adv: Use netif_rx().

References: bnc#1189998 (PREEMPT_RT prerequisite backports)
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
Git-commit: 94da81e2fc4285db373fe9a1eb012c2ee205b110

Since commit
   baebdf48c3600 ("net: dev: Makes sure netif_rx() can be invoked in any context.")

the function netif_rx() can be used in preemptible/thread context as
well as in interrupt context.

Use netif_rx().

Cc: Antonio Quartulli <a@unstable.cc>
Cc: Marek Lindner <mareklindner@neomailbox.ch>
Cc: Simon Wunderlich <sw@simonwunderlich.de>
Cc: Sven Eckelmann <sven@narfation.org>
Cc: b.a.t.m.a.n@lists.open-mesh.org
Signed-off-by: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Acked-by: Sven Eckelmann <sven@narfation.org>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 net/batman-adv/bridge_loop_avoidance.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/batman-adv/bridge_loop_avoidance.c b/net/batman-adv/bridge_loop_avoidance.c
index eb55b419faf8..612e90731c27 100644
--- a/net/batman-adv/bridge_loop_avoidance.c
+++ b/net/batman-adv/bridge_loop_avoidance.c
@@ -437,7 +437,7 @@ static void batadv_bla_send_claim(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv, u8 *mac,
 	batadv_add_counter(bat_priv, BATADV_CNT_RX_BYTES,
 			   skb->len + ETH_HLEN);
 
-	netif_rx_any_context(skb);
+	netif_rx(skb);
 out:
 	if (primary_if)
 		batadv_hardif_put(primary_if);
